This paper is about machine comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of relation embeddings from ConceptNet suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
